The contractor for the&nbsp;I-40 Project at the Davie-Forsyth County Line is scheduled to close one lane of I-40 Westbound just west of Lewisville-Clemmons Road (Exit 184) to just west of Harper Road (Exit 182) beginning Friday October 23rd &nbsp;through Tuesday October 27th&nbsp;. The contractor will close the left lane of I-40 WB at 7:00 PM Friday October 23rd and will reopen all lanes by 4:00 PM Tuesday October 27th. As a result I-40 WB will be in a one lane traffic pattern for this period of time. This lane closure is required for the contractor to safely perform the removal and replacement of the I-40 pavement structure under the Harper Road Bridge. As always this work is weather dependent and may be subject to change.
